Structure:

The program will run with three instructional sessions per week and one weekly test/review session.


3 Weekly Sessions

Each session focuses on a specific area:

• Qur'anic Vocabulary

• Fusha Vocabulary

• Grammar (Al-Ajurrumiyyah)


1 Weekly Review Session

One dedicated session will be held for:

• Weekly testing of learned material

• Revision of missed lessons

• Clarifying difficult concepts



Schedule:


Regular Sessions

Monday – Qur’anic Vocabulary

Wednesday – Fusha Vocabulary

Friday – Grammar (Al-Ajurrumiyyah)


Review/Test Session

Sunday – Weekly Test + Review



Session Format:

Each session will be 30 minutes and held after Fajr.

Typical structure:

• 5 minutes – Review of previous lesson

• 20 minutes – New material

• 5 minutes – Practice / discussion


Sunday sessions will include:

• Weekly test

• Group review for missed sessions

• Optional Q&A time


Participants may leave after completing the test if they do not need the review session.



Participation Rules:


1. Each participant will take turns leading review sessions.

2. Teaching responsibilities will rotate among participants so everyone gains teaching experience.

3. Two participants will prepare separate weekly tests on a rotating basis.

4. Participants should speak in Fusha with each other as much as possible, according to their ability.

5. All session notes, vocabulary lists, and tests will be uploaded to a shared open forum.

6. Each participant must maintain a personal vocabulary bank and regularly review it.



